%description
The function pointdensity returns a density count and the temporal average
for every point in the original list. The dataframe returned includes four
columns: lat, lon, count, and date_avg. The "lat" column is the original
latitude data; the "lon" column is the original longitude data; the
"count" is the density count of the number of points within a radius of
radius*grid_size (the neighborhood); and the date_avg column includes the
average date of each point in the neighborhood.

